title: Lubbock senior wins in national tennis tournament
text:
Lubbock senior wins in national tennis tournament Posted: tlangston@kcbd.com Collins (fourth from the left) and her team 
Coronado senior Reagan Collins represented Lubbock over the weekend in the Junior Team Tennis Tournament in South Carolina. 
Collins, a doubles and singles player at Coronado, was invited to compete in the tournament and qualified in June. 
She and her teammates defeated 15 other teams from around the country to win the national event Saturday. 
Collins is the only Lubbock player on the team, comprised of mostly Dallas-area players.
